                    <h3>World Language Mapping System</h3>
<h2><strong>World Language Phyla/Family Mapping</strong></h2>
<h2><strong>Dr. Stephen Huffman</strong></h2>
<table style="width: 100%;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td valign="top">
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.gmi.org/index.php/products/gis/wlms/samplemaps/huffman/#abstract">Abstract</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.gmi.org/index.php/products/gis/wlms/samplemaps/huffman/#whatsnew">What's New as of 3 May 2006</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.gmi.org/index.php/products/gis/wlms/samplemaps/huffman/#usage">Usage Notes</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.gmi.org/index.php/products/gis/wlms/samplemaps/huffman/#maps">Maps with PDF downloads</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.gmi.org/index.php/products/gis/wlms/samplemaps/huffman/#data">Classification data and ArcGIS project file downloads</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.gmi.org/index.php/products/gis/wlms/samplemaps/huffman/#wdb2">Additional map (Indo European Language Family)</a></li>
</ul>
</td>
<td rowspan="2" valign="top"><a name="Indian Subcontenent Image"></a><img title="Languages of the Indian subcontinent map" src="/files/7712/6771/8377/Huffman-Indian_Subcontinent_Langs-wlms32.jpg" alt="A map displaying the languages of the Indian subcontinent" width="250" height="308" /></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top">
<h3><a name="abstract"></a>Abstract</h3>
<p class="bodystyle">Dr. Huffman has classified the languages of the <a href="http://www.ethnologue.com/" target="_blank"><em>Ethnologue</em></a> into broader groupings following Merritt Ruhlen&rsquo;s <em>A Guide to the World&rsquo;s Languages</em> (published 1987, 1991 by Stanford University Press), and has produced as series of maps of language phyla and families using this classified data and several versions of GMI's <a title="World Language Mapping System" href="/products/gis/worldlanguagemappingsystem/">World Language Mapping System</a> and <a title="Seamless Digital Chart of the World" href="/products/gis/seamlessdigitalchartoftheworld/">Seamless Digital Chart of the World</a> geographic data sets. PDF versions of the maps available for download, as are Dr. Huffman's data table and ArcGIS project files.</p>
<p class="bodystyle">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="bodystyle">For additional discussion of both language classification and the initial mapping process, see Dr. Huffman's paper describing this work: <a href="http://www.gmi.org/files/Mapping_Genetic_Relationships_World_Languages.pdf" target="_blank">Mapping The Genetic Relationships of the World&rsquo;s Languages</a> (pdf).</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3><a name="whatsnew"></a>What's New</h3>
<p class="bodystyle">As of 3 May 2006</p>
<ul>
<li>PDF files have been recreated with WLMS 3.2 (15th Edition <em>Ethnologue)</em> with higher resolution and improved compression (better quality with smaller files). </li>
<li>Data and map project download for WLMS version 3.0-3.1 (14th Edition <em>Ethnologue</em>) updated to fix file reference problems.</li>
<li>Data and map project download for WLMS version 3.2 (15th Edition <em>Ethnologue</em>) added </li>
</ul>
<h3><a name="usage"></a>Usage Notes</h3>
<ul>
<li>The PDF files are fairly large. We recommend downloading first, then opening the file in <a href="http://get.adobe.com/reader/" target="_blank">Adobe Reader</a>. Most browsers support this with a right-click (Windows) or option-click (Mac) on the download link. See your browser's help system for details. Those with slow or unreliable connections are advised to use a download manager. We use <a href="http://www.freshdevices.com/" target="_blank">Fresh Download</a>.</li>
<li>Maps in this series were designed to be printed on large-format (36" wide or greater) primters. Adobe Reader allows printing at smaller sizes, but text and language borders may be unreadable. Full detail may be seen by zooming in on-screen in Adobe Reader. Large format printers can be found in most cities in sign shops and larger print/copy shops. GMI's <a title="Custom Mapping Service" href="/services/mapping/custommappingservice/">custom mapping service</a> will also print and mail these maps in sizes up to 36 inches in the narrower dimension. </li>
<li>To find a specific language, zoom into the map until language names are visible, then use Acrobat's Find (ctrl-F) function to move to the part of the map containing the language you are looking for. Name are from the 14th Edition <em>Ethnologue;</em> names can be looked up at <a href="http://www.ethnologue.com/" target="_blank">www.ethnologue.com</a>.</li>
<li>Permission is granted to reprint these maps for personal, academic, or nonprofit use. For for-profit publication, contact Dr. Huffman. </li>
</ul>
<h3><a name="maps"></a>Maps Produced with the <a title="World Language Mapping System" href="/products/gis/worldlanguagemappingsystem/">World Language Mapping System</a> and <a title="Seamless Digital Chart of the World" href="/products/gis/seamlessdigitalchartoftheworld/">Seamless Digital Chart of the World</a></h3>
<p class="bodystyle">Maps previewed on this page and available for download were produced with version 3.2 of the <a title="World Language Mapping System" href="/products/gis/worldlanguagemappingsystem/">World Language Mapping System</a> (<a title="World Language Mapping System" href="/products/gis/worldlanguagemappingsystem/">WLMS</a>), corresponding to the 15th Edition of the Ethnologue, and version 3.1 of GMI's <a title="Seamless Digital Chart of the World" href="/products/gis/seamlessdigitalchartoftheworld/">Seamless Digital Chart of the World</a> (<a title="Seamless Digital Chart of the World" href="/products/gis/seamlessdigitalchartoftheworld/">SDCW</a>). ArcGIS project files and classification data tables are available for both WLMS 3.2 and WLMS 3.0-3.1 (14th Edition <em>Ethnologue).</em></p>
<h4>The World's Language Phyla</h4>
<h5>66 x 34 in (<a href="http://www.gmi.org/files/Huffman-World_Langs-wlms32-100dpi.pdf" target="_blank">download PDF</a> - 4 MB)</h5>
<p><a name="World Lang Image"></a><img title="The World's language phyla" src="/files/3012/6771/8380/Huffman-World_Langs-wlms32.jpg" alt="A sample map of the World's language phyla" width="850" height="423" /></p>
