<h5>&nbsp;</h5>
<h3><a name="data"></a>Classification Data and ArcGIS project files</h3>
<p class="bodystyle">Download classification data table and GIS project files used to produce the maps above. Classification table is .DBF format, importable by most spreadsheet and database programs. GIS project files are in .MXD format for use with ESRI's <a href="http://www.esri.com/software/arcgis/index.html" target="_blank">ArcGIS 9.x</a> and require GMI's <a title="World Language Mapping System" href="/products/gis/worldlanguagemappingsystem/">World Language Mapping System</a> [<a title="World Language Mapping System" href="/products/gis/worldlanguagemappingsystem/">WLMS</a>] and <a title="Seamless Digital Chart of the World" href="/products/gis/seamlessdigitalchartoftheworld/">Seamless Digital Chart of the World</a> [<a title="Seamless Digital Chart of the World" href="/products/gis/seamlessdigitalchartoftheworld/">SDCW</a>] data products.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.gmi.org/files/huffman-WLMS-31.zip">huffman-WLMS-31.zip</a> for use with <a title="World Language Mapping System" href="/products/gis/worldlanguagemappingsystem/">WLMS</a> v. 3.1 (14th Edition <a href="http://www.ethnologue.com/" target="_blank">Ethnologue</a>) and <a title="Seamless Digital Chart of the World" href="/products/gis/seamlessdigitalchartoftheworld/">SDCW</a> v. 3.0 or 3.1</li>
<li><a href="http://www.gmi.org/files/huffman-WLMS-32.zip">huffman-WLMS-32.zip</a> for use with <a title="World Language Mapping System" href="/products/gis/worldlanguagemappingsystem/">WLMS</a> v. 3.2 (15th Edition <a href="http://www.ethnologue.com/" target="_blank">Ethnologue</a>) and <a title="Seamless Digital Chart of the World" href="/products/gis/seamlessdigitalchartoftheworld/">SDCW</a> v. 3.0 or 3.1</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p class="bodystyle"><strong>Notes:</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>To use these files to produce maps with ArcGIS, WLMS, and SDCW (assuming all are installed), save the .zip to c:\GMI_Geodata\projects (if the WLMS and SDCW are installed in their default locations), then right click on the zip file and choose "expand to here" using <a href="http://www.winzip.com/" target="_blank">WinZip</a>). You should end up with all files in a folder c:\GMI_Geodata\projects\huffman. Simply open the ArcMap project files to use. If you have WLMS but not DCW, data for some layers will be missing and will be marked with a red ! in the ArcMap Table of Contents. </li>
<li>An earlier version of the version 3.1 zip file contained project files with incorrect file paths. These are corrected in the current version.</li>
</ul>
